Hi all, I have an issue where I'm trying to show a different line of text on a landing page based on someone's Lifecycle Stage.

{% if contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Subscriber' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Get in touch with us
        &lt;/h1&gt;
        {% elif contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Lead' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Let's create new value together
        &lt;/h1&gt;
               {% elif contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Marketing Qualified Lead' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Let's create new value together
        &lt;/h1&gt;

                    {% elif contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Sales Qualified Lead' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Let's create new value together
        &lt;/h1&gt;

              {% elif contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Opportunity' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Let's create new value together
        &lt;/h1&gt;
             {% elif contact.IWW_Lifecycle_stage == 'Customer' %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Let's create new value together
        &lt;/h1&gt;
        {% else %}
&lt;h1&gt;
   Get in touch with us
      &lt;/h1&gt;
{% endif %}

However it just shows the default option. Any ideas why it is not looking at the field?
